Copy 'calc.bas' into the programs folder inside a MikeOS source folder and run 
the build script appropriate for your operating system (located in the root directory). 

A floppy disk image will be generate in the 'disk_images' folder, 
which you can run in an emulator or write to a physical floppy disk and boot off of.

You can run the program by selecting it in the OS menu or typing 'calc' at the commandline.

Calculator requires the latest BASIC interpreter of the Google Code page.

Calculator requires the MikeOS BASIC interpreter. 
It may not work on MikeOS derivative or OS independent versions of the
MikeOS BASIC interpreter.
